<h1>COM 225 Speech Self Reflections</h1>
<strong>Purpose:</strong> To analyze critically one's own's thoughts, feelings, and behaviors before, during, and after presenting speeches in an effort to improve public speaking abilities.  One way to become a competent and confident public speaker is to reflect on your speeches shortly after presenting to reinforce speaking strengths, identify opportunities for improvement, and select specific strategies to improve.

<strong>To conduct a speech self-reflection, do the following:</strong>
* Review any verbal or written feedback provided by your audience.  For    classroom speeches, review the parameters of the speech and the feedback provided on the rubric.
* Complete the Public Speaking Self-Reflection Inventory below.  Read through the inventory and place a check in the “Ok” column if the statement is characteristic of you and check “Set Goal” if not. (On this page, a checked box indicates "OK" and an unchecked box represents "Set Goal.")

